# Feature engineering: creating lagged features to use historical data
def create_lagged_features(df, lag=3):
    df_lagged = df.copy()
    for i in range(1, lag + 1):
        df_lagged[f'Export Value Lag {i}'] = df_lagged['Export Value'].shift(i)
    df_lagged = df_lagged.dropna().reset_index(drop=True)
    return df_lagged

df_lagged = create_lagged_features(test)

# Define selected features including 'Area' and 'Year'
selected_features = ['Area', 'Year', 'Yield', 'Agricultural Use_x', 'Emissions (CO2)', 'Emissions (N2O)',
                     'Export Quantity', 'Import Quantity', 'Temperature change',
                     'Crops total (Emissions CH4)', 'Crops total (Emissions N2O)']

# Define target variable
target_variable = 'Export Value'

# Subset the dataset with selected features and target variable
data = test[selected_features + [target_variable]]

# Split the data into features and labels
features = data[selected_features]
labels = data[target_variable]

# Preserve the 'Area' and 'Year' columns for later use
areas = features['Area']
years = features['Year']

# Drop 'Area' and 'Year' from features for model training
features = features.drop(columns=['Area', 'Year'])

# Split the data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test, area_train, area_test, year_train, year_test = train_test_split(
    features, labels, areas, years, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Standardize the data
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)

# Define the MLP model with increased max_iter
mlp = MLPRegressor(hidden_layer_sizes=(64, 32, 16), max_iter=1000, activation='relu', solver='adam', random_state=42)

# Train the model
mlp.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)

# Make predictions on the test set
y_pred = mlp.predict(X_test_scaled)

# Evaluate the model
train_mse = mean_squared_error(y_train, mlp.predict(X_train_scaled))
test_mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
train_r2 = r2_score(y_train, mlp.predict(X_train_scaled))
test_r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)

print(f"Training Mean Squared Error: {train_mse}")
print(f"Testing Mean Squared Error: {test_mse}")
print(f"Training R² Score: {train_r2}")
print(f"Testing R² Score: {test_r2}")

# Create a DataFrame with true and predicted values for the test set
test_results_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Instance ID': ['Instance {}'.format(i) for i in range(1, len(y_test) + 1)],
    'Area': area_test,
    'Year': year_test,
    'Real value (dollars)': y_test,
    'Predicted value (dollars)': y_pred
}).reset_index(drop=True)

# Prepare future data for the years 2022, 2023, and 2024
future_years = [2022, 2023, 2024]

future_predictions = []

for area in areas.unique():
    for year in future_years:
        # Use the mean values of the features for the future predictions and add some variation
        mean_features = test[test['Area'] == area][selected_features[1:]].mean().to_dict()
        for feature in mean_features:
            if feature != 'Year':
                mean_features[feature] += np.random.normal(0, mean_features[feature] * 0.1)  # Add variation
        mean_features['Year'] = year
        mean_features['Area'] = area
        future_predictions.append(mean_features)

future_df = pd.DataFrame(future_predictions)

# Preserve the 'Area' and 'Year' columns for future predictions
future_areas = future_df['Area']
future_years = future_df['Year']

# Drop 'Area' and 'Year' from features for prediction
future_features = future_df.drop(columns=['Area', 'Year'])

# Standardize the future features
future_features_scaled = scaler.transform(future_features)

# Make predictions for future years
future_predictions = mlp.predict(future_features_scaled)

# Create a DataFrame with future predictions and include an 'Instance ID' column
future_results_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Instance ID': ['Instance {}'.format(i) for i in range(len(test_results_df) + 1, len(test_results_df) + len(future_predictions) + 1)],
    'Area': future_areas,
    'Year': future_years,
    'Real value (dollars)': [None] * len(future_predictions),
    'Predicted value (dollars)': future_predictions
}).reset_index(drop=True)

# Combine only future predictions into a single DataFrame
combined_results_df = future_results_df

# Save the results to a CSV file
output_combined_results_filename = 'combined_predictions.csv'
combined_results_df.to_csv(output_combined_results_filename, index=False)

print(f'Combined predictions (including future years) are saved to {output_combined_results_filename}')
print(combined_results_df.head())

# Plot the results
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 7))

plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.scatter(y_train, mlp.predict(X_train_scaled), alpha=0.5)
plt.plot([y_train.min(), y_train.max()], [y_train.min(), y_train.max()], 'r--')
plt.xlabel('Actual')
plt.ylabel('Predicted')
plt.title('Training Data')

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.scatter(y_test, y_pred, alpha=0.5)
plt.plot([y_test.min(), y_test.max()], [y_test.min(), y_test.max()], 'r--')
plt.xlabel('Actual')
plt.ylabel('Predicted')
plt.title('Testing Data')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
